fix(batch): preserve argv array in shell mode to prevent quoting loss

When batch positional args are joined into a string and passed back to a
shell, tokens that originally contained spaces or metacharacters lose
their quoting because the outer shell already consumed the quotes during
initial argv parsing.

Fix: when the command is not resolved to a named script, always pass the
original argv array through to _execNormalized. In shell mode, use
execa(file, args, { shell }) instead of execaCommand(joined, { shell })
so that execa applies per-platform shell escaping to each argument
individually.

